<h1>@HI{{yo}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li> <strong>@HI{{yo}}</strong>.
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{yo}}</strong> is a sentence ending particle. It can be used to:
<ul>
<li> urge a course of action
<li> indicate a request (in this usage it is stronger than <a href="grammar-particle-ne.html">@HI{{ne}}</a>)
<li> indicate that the speaker feels certain of what he is saying
<li> indeicate scolding or contempt
</ul>
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{ano@KJ{{unfold^perusal^meeting}}he@KJ{{going}}ttemimashou<strong>ne</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Come on, lets' go to that exhibition.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}no@KJ{{house}}nimo@KJ{{come}}tekudasai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Come to <em>my</em> house too.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{now^day}}ha@KJ{{gold^weekday^day}}desu<strong>yo</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      Today is Friday, you know?
  </td> </tr>
</table>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{ano@KJ{{person}}ha@KJ{{attend^matter}}ha dekinaiwa<strong>yo</strong>.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      He just can't do the work!
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

